If you start getting odd switching between AC/battery, it's a sign that the system is on it's way out.  Basically, there's a small power-control system on the motherboard that sometimes goes bad.  When it does, it will not recognize when an AC adaptor is plugged up at all.  Means once the battery is dead, you have a nice paperweight.  Found out the hard way, have a paperweight here.
Has nothing to do with your current problem, just something to watch out for in the future.  How many RAM sticks do you have installed?
